abstract: On a rainy evening of dampened festivities, its epoch-making departure stirred hopes and fears, but also relief that the ordeal is finally over.
snippet: On a rainy evening of dampened festivities, its epoch-making departure stirred hopes and fears, but also relief that the ordeal is finally over.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — To the recorded peals of Big Ben and the gentle fluttering of Union Jacks, Britain bade farewell to the European Union at 11 p.m. on Friday, severing ties to the world’s largest trading bloc after nearly half a century and embarking on an uncertain future as a midsize economy off the coast of Europe.

abstract: Immediately after the vote, senators rushed to confer over what would happen next.
snippet: Immediately after the vote, senators rushed to confer over what would happen next.
lead_paragraph: The Senate vote on Friday to block new witnesses in President Trump’s impeachment trial signaled a crucial turning point, steering toward an all but certain acquittal within days. But immediately after the tally was finished, confusion reigned about the precise timetable for the trial’s endgame.
headline_main: Senate trial timetable in limbo after a vote to block witnesses.
byline_original: By Emily Cochrane and Patricia Mazzei

abstract: Republicans shut down a Democratic bid to consider new witnesses and documents, paving the way for a verdict in days.
snippet: Republicans shut down a Democratic bid to consider new witnesses and documents, paving the way for a verdict in days.
lead_paragraph: The Senate voted on Friday to block the consideration of additional witnesses and documents in President Trump’s impeachment trial, as Republicans shut down a push by Democrats to bring in new evidence and cleared the way for a swift acquittal in the coming days.

headline_main: Senate votes to block impeachment witnesses, moving toward acquittal.
byline_original: By Michael D. Shear and Nicholas Fandos

abstract: The Senate voted against hearing from new witnesses in President Trump’s impeachment trial after the House managers and the defense team made their final cases on hearing witnesses.
snippet: The Senate voted against hearing from new witnesses in President Trump’s impeachment trial after the House managers and the defense team made their final cases on hearing witnesses.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After 10 days of arguments and deliberations, the Senate voted against hearing from new witnesses in President Trump’s impeachment trial, signaling a vote to acquit him would likely come in the coming days.

abstract: There is no question, Sen. Lamar Alexander said, that President Donald Trump actions were “inappropriate” when he asked Ukraine's leader to investigate Democratic rival Joe Biden.
snippet: There is no question, Sen. Lamar Alexander said, that President Donald Trump actions were “inappropriate” when he asked Ukraine's leader to investigate Democratic rival Joe Biden.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — There is no question, Sen. Lamar Alexander said, that President Donald Trump actions were “inappropriate” when he asked Ukraine's leader to investigate Democratic rival Joe Biden.
headline_main: GOP Senators Seek to Acquit Trump Without Condoning Conduct
headline_print_headline: GOP Senators Seek to Acquit Trump Without Condoning Conduct

abstract: Barring witnesses from testifying would push the United States “closer than ever to authoritarian one-man rule,” a former lawmaker said.
snippet: Barring witnesses from testifying would push the United States “closer than ever to authoritarian one-man rule,” a former lawmaker said.
lead_paragraph: Claudine Schneider, a Republican who spent 10 years in the House representing Rhode Island, warned on Friday that by barring witnesses from testifying in President Trump’s impeachment trial, Senate Republicans would push the United States “closer than ever to authoritarian one-man rule.”
headline_main: Former G.O.P. lawmakers call for witnesses.

lead_paragraph: On Friday’s show, we did something we’ve never done before and something we’ve long resisted: We interviewed our boss.

abstract: President Trump issued an executive order on trafficking, but several advocacy groups did not attend the meeting, criticizing it as a “one way” conversation.
snippet: President Trump issued an executive order on trafficking, but several advocacy groups did not attend the meeting, criticizing it as a “one way” conversation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump held what he called a summit on human trafficking at the White House on Friday and pledged his administration’s commitment to combating it.
